Share information
Cube Storage Pioneers

Little Robots, Big Business

Since its inception in 1996, AutoStore™ has worked to improve warehouse efficiency. Today, the company’s key value proposition is to deliver an easy-to-use software powered cubic automatic storage and retrieval ecosystem.

The AutoStore solution is modular and flexible, and can automate any warehouse. The system offers a superior customer value proposition across operating metrics, ESG scores, and customer economics.
‍

View video to learn more

entry.title: hallu­ci­no­genic honey (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that hallu­ci­no­genic honey (pictured) was used as a biological weapon more than 2000 years ago?

entry.title: Mounir Akbache (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that after failing to qualify for prestigious races as an athlete, Mounir Akbache became a rabbit?

entry.title: Ivančena (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that the memorial Ivančena was created to honor members of the Silesian Scout Resistance who were executed for their part in the resistance to Nazi occupation during World War II?

entry.title: Lewis W. Green (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that Lewis W. Green was one of the two members of the first graduating class of Centre College and later became its president?

entry.title: Toy Town (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that "Toy Town" was said to have "almost destroyed" the happy hardcore scene?

entry.title: William F. Fiedler (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that William F. Fiedler was the only American fighter pilot to become a flying ace in the P-39 Airacobra?

entry.title: nearly a thousand elections for local executives (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that nearly a thousand elections for local executives were held in Indonesia between 2005 and 2013, with an average of around one every three days?

entry.title: Agnes Kimball (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that although Agnes Kimball was a popular recording artist of opera and musical theatre, she never appeared as a singing actress on the stage?

entry.title: 287 Broadway (Wikipedia — did you know?)
entry.content: ... that 287 Broadway was once called "the most succulent cast-iron street-show in all New York"?
